  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThis issue serves a source of information about running Lighthouse on merge testnets.\r\n\r\n## Merge Testnet Example Commands\r\n\r\nExample CLI commands to start Lighthouse on `kiln`:\r\n\r\n### Beacon Node\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nlighthouse \\\r\n    --network kiln \\\r\n    --debug-level debug \\\r\n    beacon_node \\\r\n    --execution-endpoints http:\\\\localhost:8551 \\\r\n    --jwt-secrets /home/me/.ethereum/geth/jwt.hex \\\r\n    --dummy-eth1 \\\r\n    --http \\\r\n    --metrics\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Validator Client\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nlighthouse \\\r\n\t--debug-level debug \\\r\n        --network kiln \\\r\n\tvalidator_client \\\r\n\t--suggested-fee-recipient <ADDRESS> \\\r\n\t--metrics\r\n```\r\n\r\n*Replace `<ADDRESS>` with your Ethereum address, that's (probably) where transactions fees go!*\r\n\r\n## Testnets\r\n\r\n### `kiln`\r\n\r\nThe [Kiln testnet specifications](https://github.com/eth-clients/merge-testnets/tree/main/kiln) have been release and the `--network kiln` flag is available in `unstable`.\r\n\r\nNon-Lighthouse tools for the Kiln network can be found at: https://kiln.themerge.dev/\r\n\r\n### `merge-devnet-5`\r\n\r\n[`merge-devnet-5`](https://github.com/eth-clients/merge-testnets/tree/main/merge-devnet-5) is a short-lived testnet organised by Pari from the EF. It is supported by Lighthouse.\r\n\r\nWhilst the Lighthouse `unstable` branch supports `merge-devnet-5` via the `--testnet-dir` flag, **we recommend users use the `merge-devnet-5` branch from https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/pull/3054**. This permits the use of the `--network merge-devnet-5` flag, which simplifies setup.\r\n\r\nUse the [`sigp/merge-devnet-5`](https://hub.docker.com/r/sigp/lighthouse/tags?page=1&name=merge-devnet-5) Docker image or build from source:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ngit clone https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse.git\r\ncd lighthouse\r\ngit checkout merge-devnet-5\r\nmake\r\n```\r\n",
